reviewText: I am eagerly waiting for the Complete Series of DIAGNOSIS: MURDER that I'm hoping will be released before the end of the year.  In anticipation of that release, I purchased both volumes of season four as 'samplers' to see what kind of picture quality we will have to look forward to 'when' the box set becomes available. Dick Van Dyke was/is such all-time GIANT where character acting is concerned and this series - in the spirit of the Murder She Wrote genre is no exception! I am happy to report that the picture quality is quite good and reinforces my desire to purchase the entire series to add to my ever growing library of family friendly programming. Below is a list of the special guest stars and episode highlights for this three disc set.The special guest stars for this volume will include:Kim Johnson-Urich, Roger Aaron Brown, Ken Howard, Wayne Pe're, Peggy Fleming, Randy Gardner, Tai Babilonia, Julie Benz, John Schneider, Ellen Crawford, Gregory Itzin, Leslie Anne-Down, Jason Clarke, Josh Taylor, Gary Grossman, Tracy Gold, Eric McCormick, Marrieta DePrima, Spike Silver, Michael Cole, Saxon Trainer, Piper Laurie, Steven Ho, Stacy Van Dyke, Mark Hutter, Wanda De Jesus and many more!DISC 1Dr. Mark Sloan investigates the "friendly fire" death of a cop, plays cat-and-mouse with a cold-hearted ice skater, discovers the ugly side of the beauty business, and reveals a shocking secret from his own past when he's quarantined with Dr. Jesse Travis, who is infected with a lethal virus.DISC 2Dr. Sloan tracks a brutal serial killer  who is obsessed wit him, exposes a homicidal doctor more interested in money than medicine and, in an unsold pilot for a proposed spin-off series, helps an undercover police woman foil a terrorist bomb plot. The pilot features a beloved sitcom star...and actor who would soon become one.DISC 3Dr. Mark Sloan tackles murder in politics, in the classroom, in the hospital and, in the last of these four memorable episodes, in his own family when his estranged, long-lost daughter returns, played by Dick Van Dyke's real-life daughter Stacy in her first TV role.This is an excellent season - can't wait for the complete series! Purchase with confidence.
summary: DIAGNOSIS: MURDER SEASON FOUR (PART 1) - A REVIEW OF PICTURE QUALITY
